    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Phonology  ",
          "bold": true,
          "textSize": "heading-one"
        }
      ],
      "align": "center"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Phonology is the branch of linguistics concerned with how humans organize the sounds of their language into an abstract system of phonemes and syllables. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Phoneme - an organizing unit indexing a sonic contrast [is there a way to import an interactive activity?] *get examples from 330L book*"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "[Include example of the IPA 2020 chart] "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Syllable - the metric building blocks of utterances "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Studying the phonology of a singing voice involves studying how artists pattern different sounds throughout their performance. A sociophonological study in particular asks questions about whether those patterns co-occur with other social/semiotic phenomena in a meaningful way. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "This page will guide you through some of the phonological features used in reggaetón ",
          "textSize": "heading-three"
        }
      ],
      "align": "center"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "center",
      "children": [
        {
          "textSize": "heading-three",
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "horizontal-separator",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
